        "title": "Instantiate generic field with &lt;this.class&gt;",
        "body": "<p>I have following code<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public class ComplicatedBuilder extends MyBuilder\n{\n  public final Parameter&lt;ComplicatedBuilder, Long&gt; par1 = new Parameter&lt;&gt;(this);\n  public final Parameter&lt;ComplicatedBuilder, Long&gt; par2 = new Parameter&lt;&gt;(this);\n  ...\n}\n\npublic class Parameter&lt;B extends MyBuilder, T&gt;\n{\n  private T val;\n  private B builder;\n  public Parameter(B b)\n  {\n    builder = b;\n  }\n\n  public B setValue(T v)\n  {\n    val = v;\n    return builder;\n  }\n  ...\n}\n\n//usage:\nComplicatedBuilder builder = new ComplicatedBuilder();\nbuilder\n  .par1.setValue(5)\n  .par2.setValue(7);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>How could I declare parameters with something like <code>public final Parameter&lt;this.class, Long&gt; par1 ...<\/code>? I want to do it in manner that allows to copy-paste parameters list to another builder without a lot of changes.<\/p>\n",
